14832/******************************************************************************/
14833/* For a painless codes migration between the STM32L4xx device product */
14834/* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
14835/* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
14836/* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
14837/* product lines within the same STM32L4 Family */
14838/******************************************************************************/
14839
14840/* Aliases for __IRQn */
14841#define TIM6_IRQn TIM6_DAC_IRQn
14842#define ADC1_2_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
14843#define TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM17_IRQn TIM1_TRG_COM_IRQn
14844#define HASH_RNG_IRQn RNG_IRQn
14845#define HASH_CRS_IRQn CRS_IRQn
14846#define USB_FS_IRQn USB_IRQn
14847
14848/* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
14849#define TIM6_IRQHandler TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler
14850#define ADC1_2_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
14851#define TIM1_TRG_COM_TIM17_IRQHandler TIM1_TRG_COM_IRQHandler
14852#define HASH_RNG_IRQHandler RNG_IRQHandler
14853#define HASH_CRS_IRQHandler CRS_IRQHandler
14854#define USB_FS_IRQHandler USB_IRQHandler
14855

14857}
14858#endif /* __cplusplus */

14860#endif /* __STM32L432xx_H */
